00021 #ifndef __HERR_H

00024 /* if these symbols are not provided by the compiler, we'll have to
00025    fake them.  These are used in HERROR for recording location of
00026    error in code. */
00027 
00028 #ifndef __FILE__
00029 #   define __FILE__ "File name not supported"
00030 #endif
00031 #ifndef __LINE__
00032 #   define __LINE__ 0
00033 #endif
00034 
00035 /* HERROR macro, used to facilitate error reporting.  Assumes that
00036    there's a variable called FUNC which holds the function name.
00037    Assume that func and file are both stored in static space, or at
00038    least be not corrupted in the meanwhile. */
00039 
00040 #define HERROR(e) HEpush(e, FUNC, __FILE__, __LINE__)
00041 
00042 /* HRETURN_ERROR macro, used to facilitate error reporting.  Makes
00043    same assumptions as HERROR.  IN ADDITION, this macro causes
00044    a return from the calling routine */
00045 
00046 #define HRETURN_ERROR(err, ret_val) {HERROR(err); return(ret_val);}
00047 
00048 /* HCLOSE_RETURN_ERROR macro, used to facilitate error reporting.  Makes
00049    same assumptions as HRETURN_ERROR.  IN ADDITION, this macro causes
00050    the file specified by the id "fid" to be closed */
00051 
00052 #define HCLOSE_RETURN_ERROR(hfid, err, ret_val) {HERROR(err); Hclose(hfid); \
00053                                                 return(ret_val);}
00054 
00055 /* HGOTO_ERROR macro, used to facilitate error reporting.  Makes
00056    same assumptions as HERROR.  IN ADDITION, this macro causes
00057    a jump to the label 'done' which should be in every fucntion
00058    Also there is an assumption of a variable 'ret_value' */
00059 
00060 #define HGOTO_ERROR(err, ret_val) {HERROR(err); ret_value = ret_val; \
00061                                    goto done;}
00062 
00063 /* HCLOSE_RETURN_ERROR macro, used to facilitate error reporting.  Makes
00064    same assumptions as HRETURN_ERROR.  IN ADDITION, this macro causes
00065    the file specified by the id "fid" to be closed 
00066    Also , this macro causes a jump to the label 'done' which should 
00067    be in every fucntion. There is an assumption of a variable 'ret_value' */
00068 
00069 #define HCLOSE_GOTO_ERROR(hfid, err, ret_val) {HERROR(err); Hclose(hfid); \
00070                                             ret_value = ret_val; goto done;}
00071 
00072 /* HGOTO_DONE macro, used to facilitate the new error reporting model.  
00073    This macro is just a wrapper to set the return value and jump to the 'done'
00074    label.  Also assumption of a variable 'ret_value' */
00075 
00076 #define HGOTO_DONE(ret_val) {ret_value = ret_val; goto done;}
00077 
00078 /* For further error reporting */
00079 #define HE_REPORT(msg) HEreport(msg)
00080 #define HE_REPORT_RETURN(msg, ret_val) { HEreport(msg); return(ret_val); }
00081 #define HE_CLOSE_REPORT_RETURN(hfid,msg, ret_val) { HEreport(msg); \
00082                                                     Hclose(hfid); \
00083                                                     return(ret_val);}
00084 
00085 #define HE_REPORT_GOTO(msg, ret_val) { HEreport(msg); ret_value = ret_val; \
00086                                        goto done;}
00087 #define HE_CLOSE_REPORT_GOTO(hfid,msg, ret_val) { HEreport(msg); \
00088                                                   Hclose(hfid); \
00089                                                   ret_value = ret_val; \
00090                                                   goto done;}
